  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development would, by reason of its bulk, mass, height and configuration, would have incoherent relation with its neighbouring building and by reason of its design with respect to the top floor and fenestration pattern would form a visually intrusive development harmful to the appearance of the surrounding area contrary to Policy DC61 of the LDF Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD.",
    "The proposed development, due to the position of the proposed balconies would result in unacceptable loss of privacy and other amenities harmful to the existing occupiers of Queenside Mews. The development, in terms of its impact on neighbouring amenity would contrary to policy DC61 of the LDF, the Residential Design SPD, and the National Planning Policy Framework.",
    "The proposal fails to demonstrate that there is sufficient space on site or the adjacent road to provide suitable access for the refuse, fire engine and other commercial vehicles servicing the proposed development. Further there is insufficient information with respect to the provision of disabled parking as well as electric charging point. Due to the lack of information the proposal fails to demonstrate compliance with the requirements of the LDF Core Strategy and Development Control Policies.",
    "In the absence of a legal agreement to prevent future occupants from applying for or obtaining a residents parking permit, the proposal fails to satisfactorily mitigate the parking impacts of the development, contrary to the provisions of Policies DC2 and DC33 of the Development Control Policies DPD.",
    "The proposal would provide insufficient information with respect to energy statement, sustainable drainage strategy and hence the proposal fails to provide a sustainable development contrary to host of policies in core strategy and the London Plan 2021 including Policies S1, S2, S4, SI 5 and S13.",
    "The proposal would fail to provide accessible dwelling for those with impaired mobility, contrary to policy D7 of the London Plan 2021 which requires, all dwellings (which are created via works to which Part M volume 1 of the Building Regulations applies) meet Building Regulation requirement M4(2) 'accessible and adaptable dwellings'.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, notification of intended refusal and the reason(s) for it was given to the applicant's agent on 20.10.2021",
    "For Residential Development Only",
    "Please be advised that approval of this application from 1st September 2019 (either by London Borough of Havering, or subsequently by PINS if allowed on appeal following a refusal by London Borough of Havering) will attract a liability payment of  £92,400 plus indexation in Community Infrastructure Levy (CIL). This charge has been levied under s.206 of the Planning Act 2008 and includes both the Mayor of London's CIL and Havering Council's CIL.",
    "The proposal would add a net additional 616sqm of residential floor space. The proposal would incur a charge of £15.400 Mayoral CIL and £77,000of Havering CIL based on the calculation of £25 per square metre and £125 per square metre, subject to indexation.",
    "You are advised to visit the planning portal website where you can download the appropriate document templates.",
    "http://www.planningportal.gov.uk/planning/applications/howtoapply/whattosubmit/cil"
  ],
